# Clerk Authentication Configuration
# Get your Clerk Publishable Key from: https://dashboard.clerk.com
#
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Sign up at https://clerk.com
# 2. Create a new application (or use existing one)
# 3. Go to "API Keys" section in Clerk Dashboard
# 4. Copy the "Publishable Key" (starts with pk_test_ or pk_live_)
# 5. Paste it below
# 6. Rename this file to .env.local
# 7. Restart your development server

# Clerk Publishable Key (Required)
REACT_APP_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_YOUR_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY_HERE

# Backend API Base URL (Optional - defaults to http://localhost:8000/api)
REACT_APP_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000/api

# Development Notes:
# - Use pk_test_ prefix for development/testing
# - Use pk_live_ prefix for production
# - Never commit .env.local to version control
# - Keep this file in .gitignore
